description: In this study,wefirst evaluated the differential expression of the long non-coding rnas (lncRNAs) in the plasma from patients with tb (tb positive),community acquired pneumonia (cap) and healthy individuals (cg) using lncRNA microarray scanning.It was found that there were 2116 specific lncRNAs differentially expressed in the tb positive samples (1102 up-regulated and 1014 down-regulated),which accounted for 6.96% of total lncRNAs.Twelve differentially expressed lncRNAs discovered in microarray were subsequently validated by using real-time quantitative pcr (rt-qpcr).Two lncRNAs (enst00000354432 and enst00000427151) were further validated with more tuberculosis samples.

Our results revealed that many lncRNAs were differentially expressed in macrophages after h37ra or h37rv infection,indicating a possible role for lncRNAs in immune responses induced by mtb infection and providing important cues for further functional studies.
